eNCA speaks to Inspector-General of Intelligence, Dr. Setlhomamaru Dintwe . #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Inspector-General of Intelligence, Dr Setlhomamaru Dintwe has confirmed ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule, has laid a complaint with his office. Dr Dintwe says they are at the preliminary stage of a potential investigation. READ: Cosatu demands Magashule provide spy proof claims Magashule alleges that his phone and that of his deputy, Jessie Duarte, were tapped by the State Intelligence services. The former Free State premier is claiming state organs are being used for political battles. WATCH: Face-to-face with Ace Magashule Trade union federation Cosatu has called on Magashule to come clean. They are demanding that he provides proof that his phone was bugged. Watch the full interview above